=3D"https://www.kjmagnetics.com/images/static-pages/calculator/volta.jpg" h=
eight=3D"125px" width=3D"125px">
			</div>
		</div>
		The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Volt">volt</a> is named afte=
r the Italian physicist and chemist <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/Alessandro_Volta">Alessandro Volta</a> (1745-1827), inventor of the elect=
rical battery and discoverer of methane.
	</div>
=09
	<div class=3D"inputitem gray">
		<div class=3D"KJpicc KJbigimg">
			<div class=3D"KJpic">
				<img loading=3D"lazy" alt=3D"Portrait of ampere" class=3D"KJbigimg" src=
=3D"https://www.kjmagnetics.com/images/static-pages/calculator/ampere.jpg" =
height=3D"125px" width=3D"125px">
			</div>
		</div>
		The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ampere">ampere</a> is named =
after the French physicist and mathematician <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Andr%C3%A9-Marie_Amp%C3%A8re">Andre-Marie Ampere</a> (1775-1836)=
. One of the founders of the science of classical electromagnetism, he refe=
rred to the subject as "electrodynamics."
	</div>
=09
	<div class=3D"inputitem gray">
		<div class=3D"KJpicc KJbigimg">
			<div class=3D"KJpic">
				<img loading=3D"lazy" alt=3D"Portrait of gauss" class=3D"KJbigimg" src=
=3D"https://www.kjmagnetics.com/images/static-pages/calculator/gauss.jpg" h=
eight=3D"125px" width=3D"125px">
			</div>
		</div>
		The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gauss_%28unit%29">gauss</a> =
is named after <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carl_Friedrich_Gaus=
s">Johann Carl Friedrich Gauss</a> (1777-1855). Gauss was a German mathemat=
ician who contributed significantly to many, many fields<!--, including num=
ber theory, algebra, statistics, analysis, differential geometry, geodesy, =
geophysics, mechanics, electrostatics, astronomy, matrix theory, and optics=
-->. Gauss had an exceptional influence in many fields of mathematics and s=
cience and is ranked as one of history's most influential mathematicians.
	</div>
=09
	<div class=3D"inputitem gray">
		<div class=3D"KJpicc KJbigimg">
			<div class=3D"KJpic">
				<img loading=3D"lazy" alt=3D"Portrait of oersted" class=3D"KJbigimg" sr=
c=3D"https://www.kjmagnetics.com/images/static-pages/calculator/oersted.jpg=
" height=3D"125px" width=3D"125px">
			</div>
		</div>
		The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oersted">oersted</a> is name=
d after the Danish physicist and chemist <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Hans_Christian_%C3%98rsted">Hans Christian Oersted</a> (1777-1851), =
who discovered that electric currents create magnetic fields, an important =
aspect of electromagnetism. He is still known today for Oersted's Law.
	</div>
=09
	<div class=3D"inputitem gray">
		<div class=3D"KJpicc KJbigimg">
			<div class=3D"KJpic">
				<img loading=3D"lazy" alt=3D"Portrait of weber" class=3D"KJbigimg" src=
=3D"https://www.kjmagnetics.com/images/static-pages/calculator/weber.jpg" h=
eight=3D"125px" width=3D"125px">
			</div>
		</div>
		The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Weber_%28unit%29">weber</a> =
is named after the German physicist <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/Wilhelm_Eduard_Weber">Wilhelm Eduard Weber</a> (1804-1891). Invented the =
first electromagnetic telegraph with Gauss.
	</div>
=09
	<div class=3D"inputitem gray">
		<div class=3D"KJpicc KJbigimg">
